external_knowledge:
- "summer solstice of 2024" refers to July 26, 2024;
- "seasoned professionals" refers to those with more than 2 years of experience;
- "still blooming or recently pruned" means currently employed or employed after July 26, 2024.

- "Top-ranked" refers to the professional with the first name that comes first alphabetically within each company;
- "Active professionals" are those who have not been severed from their employment (i.e., `sever_date` is NULL);
- "Brokerage companies" are a specific type of company in the `company_type` column.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT professional_id) AS distinct_brokers
FROM employment_history
WHERE job_title = 'Broker';

SELECT 
    (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT professional_id) FROM professionals) AS total_professionals,
    (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT company_id) FROM companies) AS total_companies;

